reviews.title: Tasty and lots of food
reviews.text: Tasty and lots of food, service was top, pleasant setting and quiet inside to eat, outside too noisy due to traffic.

reviews.title: Very good food
reviews.text:
You can eat so great here. I always come here especially for the goat cheese salad with fries. So delicious! 
In addition, their coffee is also top! With a delicious cookie. 
Toilet neat ( also not unimportant )
Friendly service and a little extra mayo also no problem.

reviews.title: Fantastic
reviews.text: We are here on holiday and were looking for the best restaurant in Epe! Because of the good reviews we chose the Slimmerick and that was really fantastic 👌 Great food and good service! The reviews are so correct, this restaurant is highly recommended👍 Thanks and we will be back👍

reviews.title: Great food at De Slimmerik, nice staff, smooth service, The food was great, Highly recommended.
reviews.text:
Delicious to eat at De Slimmerik.
Really enjoyed the service, easy to order and friendly staff.

reviews.title: Fine restaurant, good bite
reviews.text: On the first day of our holiday in Epe, my girlfriend and I had a great dinner at De Slimmerick. It's a neat place with a good map. Meat, fish and vegetarian. We had the chicken dish on the house and the game pan (off the menu). The service was extremely friendly. Who knows, we might come back later this week.

reviews.title: Good food. Good food.
reviews.text:
The controls work like a well-oiled machine. Fast and very accurate.
And on top of that, excellent cuisine. 
We ate there three times during our week Epe for a reason.

reviews.title: Nice food, delicious pesto
reviews.text: Satay was very tasty, salad and cauliflower also included. But the pesto beforehand with the baguette was really delicious!! Freshly made and exquisite!

reviews.title: Special
reviews.text:
(S)Limmerick
Ate at Slimmerick by chance
Well, we knew that
The kitchen is almost star-worthy

So we will never forget that

reviews.title: Recommended in Epe
reviews.text:
Just good
Bistro but with excellent food
Sirloin steak and salmon were cooked perfectly
Service even came to ask this, you rarely experience that, usually you hear a disinterested 'does it taste?', this time really interested!
In short: recommended

reviews.title: Very tasty food.
reviews.text: Very nice lunch. Everything tasted fresh and much appeared to be homemade. Nice people and smooth service.

reviews.title: Go and experience a great experience.
reviews.text:
We ended up here on the advice of our hostesses at the B&B where we stayed.

The food was great, and I am quite a critical person and had nothing to complain about, the food was really delicious.
The service Super friendly, they immediately make you feel at ease and your wishes are taken into account.

In short, highly recommended.

reviews.title: We will be back, great!!!
reviews.text: Recommended. Will definitely come back. Great food. Too much of a good thing and bring a doggy bag. Customer-friendly service and a warm, cozy atmosphere. Thanks!!!

reviews.title: Cozy tasty and atmosphere.
reviews.text: Always great to eat there. Super food and excellent service. We always eat there when we are in the Veluwe. Top restaurant.

reviews.title: This is everything a restaurant should be!
reviews.text:
Stumbled upon this restaurant by chance while passing through. We were running late, but a friendly employee gave us a table on the cozy terrace, with heating.
This restaurant deserves a star!!! The food was delicious, fresh salad, baked potatoes, praise with ham and cheese from the oven and don't forget the delicious tenderloin tips!!! This is what a restaurant should be... delicious food, excellent staff, excellent price/quality. We would happily drive a few kilometers for another visit to this restaurant. Highly recommended!!”

reviews.title: Great food and people.
reviews.text: Lunch was delicious but more, the staff was extremely kind. The owner helped to get us to a wedding and saved from an hours walk in 30 degrees heat when they did not have to help.  Very nice place and strong recommendation

reviews.title: Very good food in a nice place
reviews.text:
We went here with another couple to have dinner. The menu was very extensive including meat, fish and vegetarian. We all had something different but everyone really enjoyed their food, it was of very good quality. They also have a nice selection of beers. The only downside was that not all of the staff were very compliant of covid countermeasures, for example distance keeping or face masks. 
All in all we would definitely recommend going here, we will certainly come back once in the area again!

reviews.title: Dinner
reviews.text:
We booked a table which was inside but as it was a very nice evening we wanted to sit outside. This was not a problem at all. 
Service was fantastic. The food was nice. 
Sitting outside was nice but the traffic noise was not so good.

reviews.title: Good food, nice atmosphere in the middle of town
reviews.text: The staff is very friendly, the good food is very affordable and the restaurant is situated in the center of Epe.

reviews.title: Charming restaurant
reviews.text:
In the middle of Epe you find a nice restaurant with excellent service and good food.
Asperges and the strawberries are recommendable.

reviews.title: Clean and modern café cum restaurant
reviews.text: A friendly and cosy restaurant in the centre of Epe, serving honest and tasty meals at reasonable prices. A nice selection of beers and wines.

reviews.title: Delightful Lunch
reviews.text: Amazingly delicious Hot Chocolate was ordered. The mushroom soup was accompanied by fresh crusty bread and both tasted wonderful. A great setting to sit and watch the happenings in the street.

reviews.title: A good restaurant
reviews.text: De Slimmerick is a restaurant which has the "whole package": good food, friendly staff, indoor and outdoor seating in the center of Epe. And, not unimportant for tourists, they have WIFI!

reviews.title: Average food in a fully packed place
reviews.text: Had dinner on a Friday evening without reservations, the place was fully packed. We managed to find a table. Staff was accurate and friendly. My husband had a very nice entree, my soup was nice after some additional salt and pepper. Main course was average, mine was dissapointing, tasted no flavours in my vegetarian  wrap. Mentioned this towards the staff and they said they would pass it to the chef. They told us that we had to inform them earlier so they could offer something else on the menu but I already had seen earlier on the menu that there was only one other veggie option which I did not fancy. Thanked them for their offer and payed the full bill.
